name: CustomObjectDataMultiInstance-CustomObjects-GET-getCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (multi-instance)] GET /{businessObjectResource}/{businessObjectId}/customObjects/{customObjectAlias} — Retrieves a collection of multi-instance custom objects.

schema.name: businessObjectResource
schema.description: The resource name of the Workday business object that has been extended by the multi-instance custom object.

schema.name: businessObjectId
schema.description: The Workday ID of the extended business object instance.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

name: CustomObjectDataMultiInstance-CustomObjects-POST-postCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (multi-instance)] POST /customObjects/{customObjectAlias} — Creates instances of multi-instance custom objects.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: updateIfExists
schema.description: If true, updates the custom object instance if it exists. If false, returns an error if the object exists. The default is false. If the object does not exist, a new object is created regardless of this setting.

schema.name: bulk
schema.description: If true, creates or updates the specified array of custom object instances in the request body. If false, specify a single object (without an array). The default is false.

schema.name: requestBody
schema.description: The custom object instance to be persisted. If bulk=true, specify an array containing the custom object instances, with a maximum of 100. If bulk=false (default), specify a JSON object.

name: CustomObjectDataMultiInstance-CustomObjects-GET-getCustomObjects_1
description: [Custom Object Data (multi-instance)] GET /customObjects/{customObjectAlias}/{customObjectID} — Get a specific instance of a multi-instance custom object

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: customObjectID
schema.description:
If the multi-instance custom object definition uses a reference ID, specify a semicolon-delimited concatenation of the business object Workday ID and reference ID using the format {businessObjectWID};{referenceIdAlias}={referenceIdValue}.

If the multi-instance custom object definition doesn't use a reference ID, specify the Workday ID of the custom object instance. 
Use a returned id from GET /{extendedBusinessObjectResource}/{extendedBusinessObjectId}/customObjects/{customObjectAlias}.

name: CustomObjectDataMultiInstance-CustomObjects-PUT-putCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (multi-instance)] PUT /customObjects/{customObjectAlias}/{customObjectID} — Updates an instance of a multi-instance custom object.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: customObjectID
schema.description:
If the multi-instance custom object definition uses a reference ID, specify a semicolon-delimited concatenation of the business object Workday ID and reference ID using the format {businessObjectWID};{referenceIdAlias}={referenceIdValue}.

If the multi-instance custom object definition doesn't use a reference ID, specify the Workday ID of the custom object instance. 
Use a returned id from GET /{extendedBusinessObjectResource}/{extendedBusinessObjectId}/customObjects/{customObjectAlias}.

schema.name: requestBody
schema.description: The custom object fields to be updated.
